JOHANNESBURG - Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba has conceded that credit ratings agency Moody s may downgrade the country s sovereign credit rating.Gigaba has met with the agency in Washington DC where he s attending the annual Spring meetings of the IMF and the World Bank.WATCH: We will be meeting only with Moody's on US trip, says Gigaba They didn t give us any reasons. They didn t give us any reassurance and so we can t provide any guarantee ourselves," said Gigaba."Our focus is to continue to grow our economy in an inclusive way, to ensure that we can restore our investment grade."Gigaba said his department will continue to try and expand the South African economy to bring in more investments and provide security for those investors.eNCA